":"after 1111","environ 1137":"about 1137","1091":"1091","1090":"1090","environ 1068":"about 1068","avant 1095":"before 1095","après 1097":"after 1097","1097":"1097","1183":"1183","environ 1091":"about 1091","1050":"1050","1070":"1070","1137":"1137","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1068":"1068","1111":"1111","VERS 1113":"about 1113","Walincourt Selvigny, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Walincourt Selvigny, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France","Cambrai, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Cambrai, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","France":"France","CAMBRAY, NORD., FRANCE":"Nord, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Sohier","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Guenter, Gernot, Hermann.","German: variant of   Scheuer  .","South German: from a short form of an ancient Germanic personal name formed with the element <i>skīr-</i> ‘clear, clean’."],"variants":[{"name":"Schierman","meanings":["Americanized form of German <b>Schiermann</b>: variant of   Schier   1."]},{"name":"Shear","meanings":["English: nickname for a beautiful or radiant person, or one with fair hair, from Middle English <i>scher</i>, <i>schir</i> ‘bright, fair’ (Old English <i>scǣre</i>, <i>scīr</i>). In addition, the name may be a habitational name from Shere (Surrey), named from the word above.","Possibly an altered form of German   Schier  ."]},{"name":"Scheuer","meanings":["German: from Middle High German <i>schiur(e)</i>, German <i>Scheuer</i> ‘barn, granary’, a topographic name for someone who lived near a conspicuous barn or near a tithe-barn. It is also a metonymic occupational name for an official responsible for receiving the tithes of agricultural produce rendered.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): topographic name from German <i>Scheuer</i> ‘barn’."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian D